        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 4:22PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northeast of Bangor, or 10 miles northwest of Paw Paw, moving
east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alamo...               Pine Grove...          Gobles...
Bloomingdale...        Kendall...             Glendale...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
